'''''I Can See Your Voice''''' is a television [[music]] [[game show]] that has aired on [[ABS-CBN]]. The show and its format is the Philippine version of the [[I Can See Your Voice|international mystery music game show franchise of South Korean origin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/20/17/soon-on-abs-cbn-ph-version-of-koreas-mystery-music-show|title=Soon on ABS-CBN: PH version of Korea's mystery music show |publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]] |date=August 20, 2017 |language=en |website=news.abs-cbn.com |access-date=June 20, 2018}}</ref><ref name="format s1">{{Cite web|url=http://entertainment.abs-cbn.com/tv/shows/icanseeyourvoice/Show-Updates/2017/09/13/24091317-mystery-music-game-show-i-can-see-your-voice-premieres-on-abs-cbn|title=Mystery music game show “I Can See Your Voice” premieres on ABS-CBN|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|website=entertainment.abs-cbn.com |date=September 13, 2017 |access-date=June 20, 2018}}</ref>

== Gameplay ==
The guest artist(s) must attempt to guess six contestants who are ''good singers'' (''SEE-ngers'') and who are ''bad singers'' (''SEE-ntunados'') without hearing them singing. They will also help with a group of panelists under the ''SING-vestigators'' (also collectively known as the ''Sing of the Crime Operatives'').

After they eliminated one to two contestants in each round, they will reveal its singing ability on the ''Stage of Truth''. The last person standing will get to sing alongside the guest artist(s).

If the winner is a ''SEE-nger'', he/she becomes an official contender of ''[[It's Showtime (variety show)|It's Showtime]]'s Tawag ng Tanghalan''; an ''Eye Ward'' to be given by guest artist(s); and 25,000 pesos. If the winner is a ''SEE-ntunado'', he/she receives only 25,000 pesos.<ref name="format s1" />

== Round and clues ==
There are six people standing on a platform referred to as ''SEE-cret songers'', with their own ''aliases'' to make them keep secret. They do not speak until the final reveal.<ref name="format s1" />

===Visual Rounds===
;''Stop, Looks, and Listen (Season 1–)''
The guest artist(s) must look at every contestant based on its {{underline|appearance}} and {{underline|singing visual}}. They will show a muted video of each contestant's singing that reveals only 0.3 seconds of their singing voice.<ref name="format s1" />
:▶ ''One eliminated contestant in this round will receive 5,000 pesos.''

===Performance Rounds===
;''The Voice is Synching (Season 1–)''
Identify the skilled vocalists who are lip-syncing to their own voice and the tone-deaf vocalists who are lip-syncing to someone else's voice that have their similar voice tone.<ref name="format s1" />

;''Sync Zoned (Season 2, episode 3 only)''
The contestants must perform a non-lyrical part of a song such as words of expression, [[whistling]], [[screaming]], or even musical [[onomatopoeia]].
:▶ ''Two eliminated contestants in this round will receive 10,000 pesos each.''

===Evidence Rounds===
;''I Like to Prove It! Prove It! (Season 1–2, episode 1–16, 18)''
They will provide proofs of each contestant's singing ability (i.e. photo, video, certificates, etc). Skilled vocalists had their own evidences while the tone-deaf vocalists had their evidences fabricated. Guests will then have 30 seconds to discuss with the SING-vestgators before making the final decision.<ref name="format s1" />

;''Let's Play It by Hear (Season 1, episode 86; Season 2, episode 17, 19–)''
For 30 seconds, three randomly selected panelists must hear the contestant's singing voice using its headphones first. Afterwards, he or she must ''defend'' and ''convince'' the contestant to seek their evidence. In episode 17, the guest artist may ask one question to each panelist.
:▶ ''Two eliminated contestants in the final round will receive 15,000 pesos each. The last person standing will receive 25,000 pesos and gets to sing a duet with the guest artist(s). If the contestant is a SEE-nger, he/she becomes an official contender of Tawag ng Tanghalan.''<ref name="format s1" />

