{{infobox television | show_name = Submission | image = Submission_poster.png | caption = ''Submission'' promotional poster | genre = {{Plainlist| [[Erotic thriller]] *[[Drama]] }} | creator = {{Plainlist| * [[Jacky St. James]] * [[Paul Fishbein]] }} | producer = Saskia Slade | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Ashlynn Yennie]] * Justin Berti * [[Skin Diamond]] * Victoria Levine * Kevin Nelson * Nika Khitrova * Brent Harvey }} | country = United States | language = English | num_seasons = 1 | num_episodes = 6 | list_episodes = #Episodes | runtime = 24–37 minutes | network = [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] | picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[16:9]] [[High-definition television|HDTV]]) | audio_format = [[Dolby Digital]] [[5.1 surround sound|5.1]] | first_aired = {{Start date|2016|5|12}} | last_aired = {{Start date|2016|6|16}} | website = http://www.sho.com/sho/submission/home }}
'''''Submission''''' is an American erotic thriller mini-series created by [[Jacky St. James]] and [[Paul Fishbein]], starring [[Ashlynn Yennie]], Justin Berti, Victoria Levine and [[Skin Diamond]]. The series premiered on [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] on 12 May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/article/2016-summer-tv-premiere-dates/|title=2016 summer TV premiere dates|date=3 May 2016|first=Kerr|last=Lordygan|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]}}</ref>
==Synopsis== The series follows the journey of Ashley ([[Ashlynn Yennie]]) from being in an unhappy relationship to her exploration of [[BDSM]] when she stumbles upon an erotic novel ''SLAVE'' by Nolan Keats.
==Cast==
===Main cast=== * [[Ashlynn Yennie]] as Ashley Pendleton, a young girl, recently out of a bad relationship, stumbles into the [[BDSM]] world after her interest is piqued by an erotic novel ''SLAVE'' by a mysterious novelist named Nolan Keats. * Justin Berti as Elliott, a BDSM practitioner who works with Dylan and develops an interest in Ashley and eventually initiates her into BDSM practices. * Victoria Levine as Jules, Ashley's friend who offers her a place to stay and has secrets of her own. * [[Skin Diamond]] as Dylan Quinn, Jules' roommate who is into kinky sex and recruits girls for Elliott. * Kevin Nelson as Raif, a coffee bar owner who has a mutual attraction to Ashley. * Nika Khitrova as Scarlet, one of Jules' bosses who is, unbeknownst to her husband, having an affair with Jules. Later, Jules, Scarlet and Tomas enter into a [[Polyfidelity|faithful polygamous]] relationship. * Brent Harvey as Tomas, Jules's boss and Scarlet's husband.
===Recurring=== * Richie Calhoun as Jonathan * Sara Luvv as Maura * Valerie Baber as Kimberly * Boston Blake as Anthony * Vicki Chase as Susannah * Karla Kush as Chelsea, a member of the book club started by Dylan * Spike Mayer as Vincent, Ashley's ex-boyfriend * Melissa Schumacher as Tina
==Development== The series co-creator, [[Jacky St. James]], mentioned that she was unhappy with the way BDSM was portrayed in ''[[Fifty Shades of Grey]]'', which she considers "passed off an abusive relationship as an honest interpretation of the BDSM lifestyle". She hoped to create a more nuanced view of the BDSM world with the series. In an interview with [[GQ]], she described the series as, "imperfect people in BDSM relationships."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/how-bdsm-went-mainstream-on-tv|title=How BDSM Went Mainstream on TV|date=28 December 2016}}</ref> The lead actress [[Ashlynn Yennie]] also echoed the creator's sentiment saying, "''Fifty Shades of Grey'' was not a correct portrayal of the type of sex that people practice. It made it seem like it was for people that were messed up or dark and it’s not at all."<ref name="uproxx">{{cite web|url=http://uproxx.com/tv/showtime-submission-review-late-night/|title=Showtime’s ‘Submission’ Is Trying To Change The Way We Look At Late-Night Erotica|date=19 May 2016|author=Mark Shrayber|work=[[Uproxx]]}}</ref> She hoped that the show "can shatter that glass ceiling of false belief and show the world what it truly means to trust, communicate, and finally feel free to talk about what you want and don’t want sexually in a consensual and healthy way."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2016/05/28/my-bdsm-journey-how-i-became-empowered-through-submission.html|title=My BDSM Journey: How I Became Empowered Through ‘Submission’|author=[[Ashlynn Yennie]]|work=[[The Daily Beast]]|date=28 May 2016}}</ref>
The trailer for the series was released on 29 April 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/submission-trailer-showtime_us_5723d441e4b0b49df6ab6641|title=The Trailer For ‘Submission’ Puts The Sex In ‘Fifty Shades’ To Shame|date=29 April 2016|author=Cole Delbyck|work=[[Huffington Post]]}}</ref>
