'''Vinod Naranat''' is an Indian [[Ventriloquism|ventriloquist]], puppeteer and puppet-maker.<ref>{{cite news|title=Learning is fun with Kitty|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-youngworld/learning-is-fun-with-kitty/article2270348.ece|publisher=The Hindu|date=October 19, 2007}}</ref> Naranat, who hails from [[Ernakulam district|Ernakulam]], began his career as a [[Magic (illusion)|magician]]. After a meeting with ventriloquist Prahaladacharya in 1987 he choose to pursue a career as ventriloquist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.magictimes.com/archives/2007/2007-10_08-14.htm}}</ref>

"Kitty", Naranat's monkey puppet, is talking to spectators with jokes and naughty comments to interact with people. Kitty has become popular, after its creator Naranat took up social issues. To create awareness among the public, the government and non-government organizations are using Kitty shows as a tool. Several corporate business organizations are also using Kitty shows for the promotion of their products and services.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stress on energy conservation|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/stress-on-energy-conservation/article1319615.ece|publisher=The Hindu|date=August 19, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= A train of ‘clean' thoughts|url=http://indiarailinfo.com/news/post/66952|website=http://indiarailinfo.com/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Puppet's message|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/kids/puppets-message/article102721.ece|publisher=The Hindu|date=February 8, 2010<!-- 16:02 IST-->}}</ref>

